            "id": "4574580",
            "title": "BTIG favors Mondelez, Smucker, and Utz as it launches food sector coverage",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\">BTIG initiated coverage on the food sector with a heavy mix of Neutral ratings due to the challenging backdrop. </p>\n<p>Analyst Rob Dickerson highlighted that sector multiples are discounted on a historic basis for many companies in the sector because of sector demand, cost, and leverage concerns. Looking ahead, Dickerson and his team think valuations will stay depressed without improved core business demand, revenue growth, boosted margins, and capital structures.</p>\n<p>Food stocks that BTIG started off coverage with a Neutral rating included BellRing Brands (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BRBR\" title=\"BellRing Brands, Inc.\">BRBR</a>), Campbell Soup (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CPB\" title=\"The Campbell's Company\">CPB</a>), Conagra Brands (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CAG\" title=\"Conagra Brands, Inc.\">CAG</a>), General Mills (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GIS\" title=\"General Mills, Inc.\">GIS</a>), Hershey (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/HSY\" title=\"The Hershey Company\">HSY</a>), Kraft Heinz (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/KHC\" title=\"The Kraft Heinz Company\">KHC</a>), McCormick (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/MKC\" title=\"McCormick &amp; Company, Incorporated\">MKC</a>), Post Holdings (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/POST\" title=\"Post Holdings, Inc.\">POST</a>), and Simply Good Foods (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SMPL\" title=\"The Simply Good Foods Company\">SMPL</a>).</p>\n<p>BTIG did find some three food stocks to recommend on what the firm views as safer, more defensive, cost-tailwind, cash step-up names amid an otherwise challenging operating backdrop.</p>\n<p>Mondelez (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/MDLZ\" title=\"Mondelez International, Inc.\">MDLZ</a></span>) is rated Buy because BTIG sees best-in-class global positioning and expects cocoa deflation from 2027 to drive significant margin expansion, above-algorithm EPS growth, and a strong low–double-digit free cash flow CAGR, leaving the current 17x forward P/E as overly discounted versus its growth and quality. J.M. Smucker (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SJM\" title=\"The J. M. Smucker Company\">SJM</a></span>) also landed a Buy rating as BTIG believes coffee profit expansion from lower arabica prices and tariff add-backs is underappreciated, supporting 20%+ segment EBIT growth next year and earnings above its high-single-digit algorithm and consensus at an attractive ~8x forward EBITDA. Meanwhile, Utz Brands (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/UTZ\" title=\"Utz Brands, Inc.\">UTZ</a></span>) is rated Buy because BTIG sees differentiated sales, profit, and free cash flow potential that is not fully reflected in its valuation, with around 32% implied upside to the $10 price target and robust projected total</p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
