            "id": "4574672",
            "title": "Avanos Medical rockets 67% on $1.27B acquisition by American Industrial Partners",
            "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li>Avanos (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/AVNS\" title=\"Avanos Medical, Inc.\">AVNS</a></span>) stock price climbed over 67% on Tuesday during pre-market hours as the medical tech company <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/20471454-avanos-medical-inc-agrees-to-be-acquired-by-american-industrial-partners-for-approximately\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"agreed to be acquired\">agreed to be acquired</a> by <span class=\"whitespace-normal\">American Industrial Partners for $1.27B.</span>\n</li>\n<li>The deal will be an all-cash transaction where AVNS shareholders will receive $25 per share in cash, implying a ~72% premium to the prior close and ~83% premium to the 30-day average price.</li>\n<li>The deal has been unanimously approved by the board and is expected to close in H2 2026, subject to shareholder approval and regulatory clearances.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
